title: The Elements of Entomology
creator: William Ruschenberger
description: LibriVox recording of The Elements of Entomology by William Ruschenberger. Read by LibriVox Volunteers The Elements of Entomology is one of seven in a Series of First Books of Natural History Prepared for the Use of Schools and Colleges. It is a succinct little textbook from 1845 that presents an introduction to entomology. The author was a surgeon in the U.S. Navy and president of the Academy of Natural Sciences.(Summary by A.L. Gramour) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobooks; science; textbooks; entomology; insects; spiders; crustaceans; worms; sea stars; sponges; articulated animals; nature
